 <p><span id="a11y-telefon">61 829 57 92</span></p>
 <p id="&rdquo;a11y-procedura&rdquo;">Everyone has the right to request the digital accessibility of a website or any of its elements. You may also request that information be made available through an alternative means of access, for example by having a digitally inaccessible document read aloud or by receiving a description of a video without audio description, etc. The request should include the details of the person submitting it, indicate which website or mobile application it concerns, and specify a preferred method of contact. If the person submitting the request asks to receive information through an alternative means of access, they should also specify a convenient way for that information to be provided. The public entity should fulfill the request promptly, no later than within 7 days from the date of submission. If it is not possible to meet this deadline, the public entity shall immediately inform the requester when the request can be fulfilled, provided that this period does not exceed 2 months from the date of submission. If digital accessibility cannot be ensured, the public entity may propose an alternative way of accessing the information. If the public entity refuses to fulfill the request to ensure accessibility or provide an alternative means of access, the requester may file a complaint regarding the provision of digital accessibility of the website or its element. After exhausting the above procedure, a request may also be submitted to the Commissioner for Human Rights.</p>
